	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a lvl 51 Ogre SK and I wouldn't trade him in for any race.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ogres have better stats for melee than any race, also higher Intelligence than Trolls.  At level 49 INT becomes important because lvl 49 spells take lots of juice.  Trolls have regen, but SK can Siphen life, so regen is not as big a deal.  If you are fear kiting correctly you shouldn't be getting hit much.  <br><br>Level 51 Ogre vs. Ice Giant in Everfrost.  My typical battle is: Darkness, Fear, 2HS 111, 156, 229, 223, 115, 189, Fear, 179, 223, 189, 168, Darkness, 223, 229, Fear, 156, 208, 210, 189, 199, Fear, 201, 197, 223, 178 Ice Giant has been slain by Lvl 51 Ogre SK solo.<br><br>Weapon of Choice: Oggok Cleaver 44/60.<br><br>Unbuffed Stats: Str 213, Sta 125, Agi 75, Dex 118, Int 108, Wis 70, Chr 33.<br><br>I have only lost 1 duel.  Yesterday I battled a level 55 Barbarian Warrior, he conned cherry red and was UBER Twinked.  We both hit 25% HPs at about the same time and he went into Berzerker mode then he started using all his warrior discaplines. So, I touched off Harm Touch and to my dismay he resisted.  I died and he was left with 87 HPs one hit from Victory.  As I said he was UBER with a super Magic resist and I was giving up 4 Levels.  He resisted all but one darkness and fear.  I have defeated many classes in Duels mostly yellow cons and a few reds.  Some of the tougher Red cons were a Ranger and Druid, they used snare, root, and nuke tactics.  Yellow cons were Warriors, Pallys, Rangers, Druids, and even one Necro.  They all died but the Cherry Red Level 55 Warrior.  I have only Harm Touched in 4 Duels, the Lvl 55 warrior resisted, but the Red conned Ranger and Druid, and also the Yellow conned Necro all crumbled and died at my feet.  All the duels were without the use of my pet.<br><br>Oh and this is my first Character.  Born October 3, 2000.  I am not Twinked, I earned all I have selling Fine Steel to venders when I was young and then killing Hill Giants in Rathe Mountains.<br><br>So back to the response Orge or Troll SK... I would go Ogre all the way again... The only different thing I would do is change where I put my initial 20 points in my stats when I created the character... 51 seasons have taught alot that I wish I knew when I started...  Oh well to much time invested now... Maybe someday I wil start an Ogre SK Twink and really do it right...<br><br>The main thing that I hope you take from my endless droning is SK are a very powerful and fun class to play.  Especially if you like to Solo, but Groups are fun also.<br><br>Oh I almost forgot, There is one downside to being Ogre SK...You are HUGE...Make friends with a Shammy or buy Shrink Potions.<br><br>That's my 2cp!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
