	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am the lvl 51 Ogre, just turned 52, when you reach this lvl you will tank much less.&nbsp;&nbsp;Warriors will me main tanks, because they have dual wield.  They can keep the mobs attention better than an SK because of the more attacks.  What I am trying to say is AC is not as important to SK as it is to Warriors at Uber lvls.  <br><br>So back to your question of where i would put my 20 points if I start over:<br>Strength = "0" you start with 140..Barbarian and Troll Warriors would love to start here..I am already maxed out when shammys and druids Strength me..255 is as high as it gets..Tons of Strength Items available<br>Stamina = "0" you start with 127..Again any warrior would love to be able to start here..By this time you will have something that gets you to 134..and that will allow you swing any weapon in the game<br>Agility = "5" you start with 70..If your Agility is less than 75 you get an AC penalty 0f -25..this is a must..I got burned on this one..hey i was a newbie =(<br>Dexterity = "10" you start with 70..This is in my opinion the best all around Stat for an OGRE SK..Dexterity items are hard to come by..When my Dex is buffed I get tons of Uber hits..also unlike most casters who stand behind the tanks and throw spells over their shoulders, you will be swinging away, getting hit, and casting all at the same time.  Higher Dex means less interrupts.  This also applies to fear kiting, If you arent quite stopped before you cast, it helps regain you concentration and gets that spell off before mob turns back on you.<br>Intelligence = "5" you start with 70..Intelligence is the second most important stat to buff for OGRE SK, However unlike Dexterity, there are tons of nice INT items for OGRE SK.  You should have no problem buffing you INT up 90 or 100.  At level 49 try to get your INT over 100, because your lvl 49 spells Dooming Darkness and Invoke Fear are big mana drains when you fear kite Solo.<br>Wisdom = "0" Bah this is for Pallys<br>Charisma = "0" Unless you are after Chicks<br><br>Keep in mind these are my picks for an Ogre SK.<br><br>I would Buff all other races differently depending on what they start with and what items are readily availible.<br><br>Only my 2 cp..I hope this helps<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
